        "reasoning_chain": "1) Passive dampers reduce vibration but have fixed damping coefficient that is sub-optimal across a range of wind conditions. 2) Improve #30 (reduce fatigue harm), worsen #27 (passive dampers degrade and must be replaced). 3) Matrix (30,27) → {23, 35, 18, 11}. 4) Apply #23 Feedback: accelerometers on cables feed a real-time controller that adjusts damping force. 5) Apply #35 Parameter change: magnetorheological (MR) fluid damper whose viscosity is controllable by magnetic field in <10 ms — variable damping ratio. 6) Apply #18 Mechanical vibration: controller generates opposing phase force to cancel detected vibration. 7) Semi-active MR damper with closed-loop control outperforms passive damper by 50% at minimal energy cost (max 50 W).",
        "solution": "Semi-active magnetorheological cable damper: each stay cable fitted with an MR damper at deck level; accelerometer on cable feeds LQR optimal controller that adjusts coil current (0–5 A) to vary damping coefficient in real time. Rain-wind induced vibration amplitude reduced 80% vs. untreated cable; 60% reduction vs. passive viscous damper. Damper requires no mechanical maintenance for 25+ years.",
